 0.9696423227962747, \"rank\": 0.029189018614271426, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only Olympic champion to skip the trip to Hong Kong will be Zheng Qinwen, the women's singles tennis champion, who is in New York preparing for the U.S. Open.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9993055027837879, \"rank\": 0.0006750814899026354, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}, {\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zheng Qinwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\"}, {\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999926120340269, \"rank\": 7.158749961979637e-06, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Table tennis star Ma Long, who won his sixth Olympic gold medal in Paris in the men's team event, will be visiting Hong Kong as an Olympic delegation member for the third time.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ma Long\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1163, \"ti